    </equation><para id="import-auto-id2616866">
      <title>Solution for (b)</title>
    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2679460">Power is energy per unit time. One year has <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>16</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{3 "." "16" times "10" rSup { size 8{7} } `s} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, so</para><equation id="eip-674"><m:math>
